A field (also called an instance variable) represents data that belongs to the current instance of the class. It can be used to store values that are specific to each instance, such as attributes or properties. A field is created within a class declaration using the keyword "field". For example, in the following code snippet, i_no and i_st are two fields of the comp class:
```csharp
class comp : superClass {
    int i_no;
    int i_st;
}
```
